      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have multi-omic TWIM-MS data (raw or processed arrival-time records) and have already assigned features or detected ion features to biomolecular classes (e.g., lipid, carbohydrate, protein), and you need CCS values stratified by class to improve calibration accuracy",
